The White House will be opening its gardens and South Grounds to the public for the annual Spring Garden Tours. The tours will take place on April 1st and 2nd from 10:00 AM to 4:30 PM ET. There will be a press preview opportunity on March 30th at 10:00 AM ET. The tours are free, but attendees need to obtain a daily timed ticket, including small children. Tickets will be distributed by the National Park Service at a tent outside the White House Visitor Center each tour day starting at 8:30 AM ET. The entrance for the tours will be on 15th Street NW between E Street NW and Constitution Avenue NW. Advance reservations are not available, and there will be an ADA entrance located at 15th Street NW and Alexander Hamilton Place NW.